AD_TAB.NAME: Grid Configuration at System Level
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Define the Grid Configuration at System Level
AD_TAB.HELP: In this tab the user can set some properties that will be used to define how the grid filtering should work at system level. The values set here will be used in all grids, unless its properties are overriden at tab or field level.

AD_TAB.NAME: Report Definition
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Report definition when the UI Pattern of the Process Definition is "Report (Using JR Templates)". Each Process Definition can only have one Report Definition.
AD_TAB.HELP: Report definition when the UI Pattern of the Process Definition is "Report (Using JR Templates)". Each Process Definition can only have one Report Definition.

AD_TAB.NAME: Tab
AD_TAB.HELP: In this tab the user can set some properties that will be used to define how the grid filtering should work in the selected tab. The values set here will be used in all its fields, unless its properties are overriden at field level. If a property is not set, its value will be taking from the system level.

AD_TAB.NAME: Process Definition
AD_TAB.HELP: Grants access to Process Definition. By default, access to process definitions in a window (invoked from a button), is inherited from the permission to the window. To revoke this inherited access and manually decide case by case which are the accessible processes, it is necessary to define a "Secured Process" Preference (at system level or for that specific window) with "Y" as value.

AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Maintain access by role to navigation bar components
AD_TAB.HELP: Maintain access by role to navigation bar components

AD_TAB.NAME: View Role Access
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Defines the access to views by Role.
AD_TAB.HELP: Defines the access to views by Role.

AD_TAB.NAME: Attachment Metadata
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Define metadata values assigned to a tab
AD_TAB.HELP: Define metadata values assigned to attachments of the tab

AD_TAB.NAME: Field
AD_TAB.HELP: In this tab the user can set some properties that will be used to define how the grid filtering should work in the selected field. If a property is not set, its value will be taking from the tab level. If it is not defined in the tab level, its value will be taken from the system level.

AD_TAB.NAME: Menu Parameters
AD_TAB.HELP: The menu parameters are used in the new user interface to pass parameters to standard view implementations.

AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: Associates a Report to a data pool.
AD_TAB.HELP: Associates a Report to a data pool.

AD_TAB.NAME: Metadata
AD_TAB.HELP: Definition of the metadata that can be configured to be included as additional information on each Attachment File.

AD_TAB.NAME: View Implementation
AD_TAB.DESCRIPTION: A view is shown in the main user interface, the view implementation defines the javaclass responsible for generating the client-side javascript.
AD_TAB.HELP:
A view is shown in the user interface as a tab in the multi-tab interface or as a popup. The view can be anything from a grid, form or a popup window. When the view is shown in the multi-tab interface then it must be a Smartclient canvas.
The view implementation defines the component which is capable of generating the client side javascript to be shown in the browser. A view implementation is a java class which extends the org.openbravo.client.kernel.BaseTemplateComponent class.
